Test "test_swarm_performance_under_heavy_load":
    Let swarm be setup_large_swarm()
    Let config be setup_test_swarm_config()
    
    Note: Create many tasks to test performance
    Let heavy_tasks be list containing
    For i from 1 to 1000:
        Add SwarmTask with:
            task_id as ("heavy_task_" plus i)
            description as ("Heavy processing task " plus i)
            assigned_agent as ""
            status as "pending"
            priority as (i modulo 10) divided by 10.0
            complexity as 0.5
            dependencies as list containing
            estimated_duration as 10.0
            actual_duration as 0.0
            resource_requirements as Dictionary with:
                "memory_mb" as 50
                "cpu_percent" as 10
                "network_mbps" as 2
            progress as 0.0
            result as ""
            error_message as ""
            created_at as get_current_timestamp()
            started_at as 0
            completed_at as 0
        to heavy_tasks
    
    Let start_time be get_current_timestamp()
    Let distributed_swarm be distribute_tasks_to_swarm with swarm as swarm and tasks as heavy_tasks and config as config
    Let end_time be get_current_timestamp()
    
    Let distribution_time be end_time minus start_time
    Assert distribution_time is less than 10000  Note: Should complete within 10 seconds

Note: Mock Helper Functions for Testing
Process called "create_swarm_topology" that takes members as List[String] and type as String returns Dictionary[String, List[String]]:
    Let topology be Dictionary with:
    
    If type is equal to "mesh":
        Note: Full mesh - everyone connects to everyone
        For each member in members:
            Let connections be list containing
            For each other_member in members:
                If other_member is not equal to member:
                    Add other_member to connections
            Set topology[member] to connections
    
    Otherwise if type is equal to "star":
        Note: Star topology - first member is hub
        If length of members is greater than 0:
            Let hub be members[0]
            Let hub_connections be list containing
            For i from 1 to (length of members minus 1):
                Add members[i] to hub_connections
                Set topology[members[i]] to list containing hub
            Set topology[hub] to hub_connections
    
    Otherwise if type is equal to "ring":
        Note: Ring topology - each connects to next and previous
        For i from 0 to (length of members minus 1):
            Let current be members[i]
            Let next_index be (i plus 1) modulo length of members
            Let prev_index be (i minus 1 plus length of members) modulo length of members
            Set topology[current] to list containing members[next_index], members[prev_index]
    
    Return topology

